BOXES

<assemblage><title>Sine of an Acute Angle</title>
<sidebyside widths="60% 40%"><p><m>\text{sin}~ \theta = \dfrac{\text{opposite}}{\text{hypotenuse}}</m></p> <image source="images/2-2sine.png"><description>triangle</description></image></sidebyside>          
</assemblage>

EXAMPLE

<example><statement>
    <p>Find the sine of the labeled angle in each triangle below. </p> <sidebyside widths="45% 40%"><image source="images/exam2-2-1a.png"><description>triangle</description></image><image source="images/exam2-2-1b.png"><description>triangle</description></image></sidebyside></statement>
<solution>
    <p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>The side opposite angle <m>\phi</m> is 5, and the hypotenuse is 13, so the sine of <m>\phi</m> is <me>\text{sin } \phi =\dfrac{5}{13}, \text{  or approximately}~~ 0.3846</me> </p></li>
        <li><p>The side opposite angle <m>\beta</m> is <m>\sqrt{5}</m>, and the hypotenuse is 3, so the sine of <m>\beta</m> is <me>\text{sin } \beta =\dfrac{\sqrt{5}}{3}, \text{  or approximately}~~ 0.7454</me></p></li>
    </ol></p></solution>
</example>

EXERCISE

<exercise><statement>
    <sidebyside widths="60% 30%"><p>Find the sine of the labeled angle in the triangle at right.  Round your answer to 4 decimal places.</p> <image source="images/exer2-2-1.png"><description>triangle</description></image></sidebyside>
</statement></exercise>

ALIGN ON EQUALS

		<me>\begin{aligned}[t]
                h^2 + 49 \amp = 625 \amp\amp \text{Subtract 49 from both sides.}\\
                h^2 \amp = 576 \amp\amp \text{Extract roots.}\\
                h \amp = \pm \sqrt{576} \amp\amp \text{Simplify the radical.}\\ 
                h \amp = \pm 24                
                \end{aligned}</me>

